The paper proposes a structure learning framework that utilizes pairwise similarities between data points to reveal underlying manifold structure. This approach is particularly suitable for learning problems that are sensitive to sample similarity, such as clustering and semi-supervised classification. The proposed framework also utilizes a deep auto-encoder architecture, which suggests a focus on machine learning and neural networks (cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on benchmark datasets, which suggests a focus on evaluation and performance analysis (cs.CL).
